#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga "
msgstr "2. Lay Followers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Mahāsālasutta "
msgstr "14. A well-to-do brahmin "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.176, pts2ed1.378, sc1
msgctxt "sn7.14:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: lūkhapāvuraṇo → lūkhapāpuraṇo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn7.14:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro brāhmaṇamahāsālo lūkho lūkhapāvuraṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then a certain well-to-do brahmin, shabby, wearing a shabby cloak, went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.14:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ brāhmaṇamahāsālaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn7.14:1.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, lūkho lūkhapāvuraṇo”ti? "
msgstr "“Brahmin, why are you so shabby, wearing a shabby cloak?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.14:1.5"
msgid "“Idha me, bho gotama, cattāro puttā. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, I have four sons. "

msgctxt "sn7.14:1.6"
msgid "Te maṃ dārehi sampuccha gharā nikkhāmentī”ti. "
msgstr "At their wives’ bidding they expelled me from my house.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.14:1.7"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imā gāthāyo pariyāpuṇitvā sabhāyaṃ mahājanakāye sannipatite puttesu ca sannisinnesu bhāsassu: "
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, memorize these verses and recite them to your sons when you are all seated in the council hall with a large crowd. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn7.14:2.1"
msgid "‘Yehi jātehi nandissaṃ, "
msgstr "‘I was overjoyed when they were born, "

# NOTE: This sense of bhava is unusual and not recorded in PTS Dict.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:2.2"
msgid "yesañca bhavamicchisaṃ; "
msgstr "and wished for them the very best. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:2.3"
msgid "Te maṃ dārehi sampuccha, "
msgstr "But at their wives’ bidding they chased me out, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:2.4"
msgid "sāva vārenti sūkaraṃ. "
msgstr "like hounds after hogs. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.379, sc3
msgctxt "sn7.14:3.1"
msgid "Asantā kira maṃ jammā, "
msgstr "It turns out they’re wicked, those nasty men, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:3.2"
msgid "tāta tātāti bhāsare; "
msgstr "though they called me their dear old Dad. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:3.3"
msgid "Rakkhasā puttarūpena, "
msgstr "They’re monsters in the shape of sons, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:3.4"
msgid "te jahanti vayogataṃ. "
msgstr "throwing me out as I’ve grown old. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn7.14:4.1"
msgid "Assova jiṇṇo nibbhogo, "
msgstr "Like an old, useless horse "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:4.2"
msgid "khādanā apanīyati; "
msgstr "led away from its fodder, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:4.3"
msgid "Bālakānaṃ pitā thero, "
msgstr "the elderly father of those kids "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:4.4"
msgid "parāgāresu bhikkhati. "
msgstr "begs for alms at others’ homes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn7.14:5.1"
msgid "Daṇḍova kira me seyyo, "
msgstr "Even my staff is better "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:5.2"
msgid "yañce puttā anassavā; "
msgstr "than those disobedient sons, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:5.3"
msgid "Caṇḍampi goṇaṃ vāreti, "
msgstr "for it wards off a wild bull, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:5.4"
msgid "atho caṇḍampi kukkuraṃ. "
msgstr "and even a wild dog. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn7.14:6.1"
msgid "Andhakāre pure hoti, "
msgstr "It goes before me in the dark; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:6.2"
msgid "gambhīre gādhamedhati; "
msgstr "in deep waters it supports me. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:6.3"
msgid "Daṇḍassa ānubhāvena, "
msgstr "By the wonderful power of this staff, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.14:6.4"
msgid "khalitvā patitiṭṭhatī’”ti. "
msgstr "when I stumble, I stand firm again.’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn7.14:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇamahāsālo bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo pariyāpuṇitvā sabhāyaṃ mahājanakāye sannipatite puttesu ca sannisinnesu abhāsi: "
msgstr "Having memorized those verses in the Buddha’s presence, the brahmin recited them to his sons when they were all seated in the council hall with a large crowd. … "

